cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the properties of the Google matrix, which is a data structure used in the PageRank algorithm. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes the PageRank of the Ulam network generated by intermittency maps, which can be seen as a type of information network. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the spectral properties of eigenvalues and eigenvectors of the Google matrix, which are related to information theory. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The Ulam method used to generate the matrix approximant for the Perron-Frobenius operator of dynamical map is a numerical method. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper discusses the efficiency of the Google search in certain situations, which can be seen as a computational engineering problem.
